page.title: 12WILDLIFE IN THE NEW FOREST
page.content: On the walk from Beaulieu to our school I saw lots of ponies and foals with their mothers.I saw some cows but not very many.There was some donkeys but not many.It was very hot and all of my class had to walk at least four miles.I saw some spiders carrying egg sacks.Some were carrying blue egg sacks some were carrying white and some were carrying a creamy colour. I walked on and I saw an ants nest and where all the ants had been walking there was white dust whereas the rest was a dark grey colour.When we were nearly back at school I saw about six mole hills and one was freshly made.
